  "prompt": "Does every student at iiser get fellowship?",
  "response": "As of my knowledge up to October 2023, **most students admitted to the regular programs at the Indian Institutes of Science Education and Research (IISERs)** receive financial support in the form of fellowships, scholarships, or stipends. Here's a general overview:\n\n1. **Undergraduate Programs (BS-MS Integrated):**\n   - **Admission:** Typically through the IISER Aptitude Test or Joint Entrance Examination (JEE) Advanced scores.\n   - **Financial Support:** Admitted students usually receive fellowships that cover tuition fees and provide a monthly stipend to support living expenses.\n\n2. **Postgraduate Programs (M.Sc., Integrated Ph.D.):**\n   - **Admission:** Based on performance in entrance exams and interviews.\n   - **Financial Support:** These programs often come with comprehensive fellowships that include tuition waiver and a stipend.\n\n3. **Doctoral Programs (Ph.D.):**\n   - **Admission:** Through a competitive selection process involving entrance exams and interviews.\n   - **Financial Support:** Ph.D. candidates generally receive fellowships that cover tuition fees and offer a stipend throughout the duration of their research.\n\n4. **Joint Programs and Exchange Programs:**\n   - **Financial Support:** Availability of fellowships can vary based on specific program requirements and partnerships with other institutions.\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n- **Eligibility:** While most regular program students receive financial support, eligibility criteria may vary based on the specific IISER campus and the program's requirements.\n  \n- **Selection Criteria:** Fellowships are often merit-based, considering academic performance, research potential, and other relevant factors.\n\n- **Additional Opportunities:** Beyond standard fellowships, there may be opportunities for additional scholarships based on research projects, academic excellence, or specific field interests.\n\n**Recommendations:**\n\n- **Check Specific IISER Websites:** Each IISER campus may have its own set of fellowships and financial support mechanisms. It's crucial to visit the official website of the specific IISER you're interested in for detailed and up-to-date information.\n\n- **Contact Admissions Offices:** If you have specific queries or need clarifications, reaching out directly to the admissions or financial aid office of the respective IISER can provide personalized assistance.\n\nIn summary, **while not every single student may receive a fellowship**, the vast majority of students admitted to IISER's regular academic programs benefit from some form of financial support, making education more accessible and allowing students to focus on their studies and research.",
